- The actual proof of `h₁` is left as `sorry` because we are only required to provide the structure of the proof.
- The final `sorry` corresponds to the trivial step of deriving the conclusion from `h₁`.

This approach avoids unnecessary complexity and adheres to the problem constraints by not introducing intermediate definitions or relying on additional lemmas (other than the `have` statement itself).

